{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839793484,"sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784cccc2001JnNnPVDmEMG1sB","messageID":"msg_d784cb57d001DBZIz7qWfXPg5y","sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_621db1cbf8434b07b21e7fc4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775839793469,"end":1775839793482}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839793487,"sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784cc215001hKSllJuGkplBmu","messageID":"msg_d784cb57d001DBZIz7qWfXPg5y","sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_81e5e06241304386a1ec4f4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Define the CRD (Custom Resource Definition) types for CodeInterpreter in the pkg/apis module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Define CodeInterpreter CRD types\n15: - [ ] Add Go type definitions\n16: - [ ] Generate CRD manifests\n17: - [ ] Add unit tests\n18: \n19: ## Notes\n20: \n21: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n22: \n23: ## Source Files\n24: \n25: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine the CRD (Custom Resource Definition) types for CodeInterpreter in the pkg/apis module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Define CodeInterpreter CRD types\n- [ ] Add Go type definitions\n- [ ] Generate CRD manifests\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n\n## Notes\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/README.md","time":{"start":1775839793464,"end":1775839793486}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839793522,"sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784cc725001TMyzZZVQw64ohH","messageID":"msg_d784cb57d001DBZIz7qWfXPg5y","sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f4e9a6850c24a928b043d80","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The AgentCube Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // AgentRuntimePhase is the lifecycle phase of an AgentRuntime.\n25: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n26: \n27: const (\n28: \t// AgentRuntimePhasePending indicates the runtime is being provisioned.\n29: \tAgentRuntimePhasePending AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n30: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseRunning indicates the runtime is running.\n31: \tAgentRuntimePhaseRunning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n32: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseFailed indicates the runtime failed to start.\n33: \tAgentRuntimePhaseFailed AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n34: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating indicates the runtime is being terminated.\n35: \tAgentRuntimePhaseTerminating AgentRuntimePhase = \"Terminating\"\n36: )\n37: \n38: // AgentRuntimeConditionType is the type of a runtime condition.\n39: type AgentRuntimeConditionType string\n40: \n41: const (\n42: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionReady indicates the runtime is ready to serve requests.\n43: \tAgentRuntimeConditionReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Ready\"\n44: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox pod has been created.\n45: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n46: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady indicates the code interpreter is attached and ready.\n47: \tAgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"CodeInterpreterReady\"\n48: )\n49: \n50: // AgentRuntimeCondition represents the state of a runtime condition.\n51: type AgentRuntimeCondition struct {\n52: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n53: \tType AgentRuntimeConditionType `json:\"type\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=type,casttype=AgentRuntimeConditionType\"`\n54: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n55: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=status,casttype=k8s.io/api/core/v1.ConditionStatus\"`\n56: \t// Reason is a one-word CamelCase reason for the condition's last transition.\n57: \t// +optional\n58: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=reason\"`\n59: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about last transition.\n60: \t// +optional\n61: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,4,opt,name=message\"`\n62: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned from one status to another.\n63: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime\" protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=lastTransitionTime\"`\n64: }\n65: \n66: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the configuration for an embedded code interpreter.\n67: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n68: \t// Enabled indicates whether to attach a code interpreter.\n69: \t// +optional\n70: \tEnabled bool `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" protobuf:\"varint,1,opt,name=enabled\"`\n71: \t// Image is the container image for the code interpreter.\n72: \t// +optional\n73: \tImage string `json:\"image,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=image\"`\n74: \t// Resources defines the resource requirements for the code interpreter.\n75: \t// +optional\n76: \tResources *ResourceQuota `json:\"resources,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=resources\"`\n77: }\n78: \n79: // ResourceQuota defines resource limits and requests.\n80: type ResourceQuota struct {\n81: \t// CPU is the CPU limit in cores (e.g., \"500m\" for 0.5 CPU).\n82: \t// +optional\n83: \tCPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=cpu\"`\n84: \t// Memory is the memory limit in bytes (e.g., \"512Mi\", \"1Gi\").\n85: \t// +optional\n86: \tMemory string `json:\"memory,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=memory\"`\n87: \t// Storage is the storage limit in bytes (e.g., \"1Gi\", \"10Gi\").\n88: \t// +optional\n89: \tStorage string `json:\"storage,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=storage\"`\n90: }\n91: \n92: // NetworkPolicy defines network access rules for the runtime.\n93: type NetworkPolicy struct {\n94: \t// EgressRules defines allowed egress destinations.\n95: \t// +optional\n96: \tEgressRules []NetworkRule `json:\"egressRules,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,rep,name=egressRules\"`\n97: \t// IngressRules defines allowed ingress sources.\n98: \t// +optional\n99: \tIngressRules []NetworkRule `json:\"ingressRules,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=ingressRules\"`\n100: }\n101: \n102: // NetworkRule defines a single network rule.\n103: type NetworkRule struct {\n104: \t// CIDR is the IP CIDR block (e.g., \"10.0.0.0/8\").\n105: \t// +optional\n106: \tCIDR string `json:\"cidr,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=cidr\"`\n107: \t// Ports is the list of allowed ports.\n108: \t// +optional\n109: \tPorts []int32 `json:\"ports,omitempty\" protobuf:\"varint,2,rep,name=ports\"`\n110: \t// Protocol is the network protocol (TCP, UDP).\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \tProtocol corev1.Protocol `json:\"protocol,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=protocol,casttype=k8s.io/api/core/v1.Protocol\"`\n113: }\n114: \n115: // LifecycleHook defines lifecycle callbacks for the runtime.\n116: type LifecycleHook struct {\n117: \t// PreStart is the URL to call before the runtime starts.\n118: \t// +optional\n119: \tPreStart string `json:\"preStart,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=preStart\"`\n120: \t// PostStop is the URL to call after the runtime stops.\n121: \t// +optional\n122: \tPostStop string `json:\"postStop,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=postStop\"`\n123: }\n124: \n125: // ContainerSpec defines the container configuration for the runtime.\n126: type ContainerSpec struct {\n127: \t// Image is the container image to run.\n128: \t// +optional\n129: \tImage string `json:\"image,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=image\"`\n130: \t// Command is the command to run in the container.\n131: \t// +optional\n132: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=command\"`\n133: \t// Args are the arguments to the command.\n134: \t// +optional\n135: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,rep,name=args\"`\n136: \t// Env is the list of environment variables.\n137: \t// +optional\n138: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,4,rep,name=env\"`\n139: \t// WorkingDir is the working directory for the container.\n140: \t// +optional\n141: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=workingDir\"`\n142: }\n143: \n144: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime.\n145: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n146: \t// Container defines the container configuration.\n147: \t// +optional\n148: \tContainer ContainerSpec `json:\"container,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=container\"`\n149: \t// Resources defines the resource quotas for the runtime.\n150: \t// +optional\n151: \tResources *ResourceQuota `json:\"resources,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=resources\"`\n152: \t// Network defines the network policies.\n153: \t// +optional\n154: \tNetwork *NetworkPolicy `json:\"network,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=network\"`\n155: \t// Lifecycle defines lifecycle hooks.\n156: \t// +optional\n157: \tLifecycle *LifecycleHook `json:\"lifecycle,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,4,opt,name=lifecycle\"`\n158: \t// CodeInterpreter defines the embedded code interpreter configuration.\n159: \t// +optional\n160: \tCodeInterpreter *CodeInterpreterSpec `json:\"codeInterpreter,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=codeInterpreter\"`\n161: }\n162: \n163: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of an AgentRuntime.\n164: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n165: \t// Phase is the current phase of the runtime.\n166: \t// +optional\n167: \tPhase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=phase,casttype=AgentRuntimePhase\"`\n168: \t// Conditions represent the latest available observations of the runtime state.\n169: \t// +optional\n170: \tConditions []AgentRuntimeCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=conditions\"`\n171: \t// SandboxRef is the reference to the sandbox pod.\n172: \t// +optional\n173: \tSandboxRef *corev1.ObjectReference `json:\"sandboxRef,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=sandboxRef\"`\n174: \t// StartTime is the time when the runtime started.\n175: \t// +optional\n176: \tStartTime *metav1.Time `json:\"startTime,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,4,opt,name=startTime\"`\n177: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the phase transitioned.\n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tLastTransitionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=lastTransitionTime\"`\n180: }\n181: \n182: // +genclient\n183: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n184: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n185: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n186: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"NAME\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".metadata.name\",description=\"Name of the runtime\"\n187: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"PHASE\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".status.phase\",description=\"Current phase\"\n188: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"SANDBOX\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".status.sandboxRef.name\",description=\"Sandbox pod name\"\n189: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"AGE\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\",description=\"Age of the resource\"\n190: \n191: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n192: type AgentRuntime struct {\n193: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n194: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n197: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n198: }\n199: \n200: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n201: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n202: \n203: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime.\n204: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n205: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n206: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n207: \tItems           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n208: }\n\n(End of file - total 208 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The AgentCube Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go","time":{"start":1775839793467,"end":1775839793518}}}}
