{"type":"text","timestamp":1775839820909,"sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784d28fc0016OAxNanbmpwKLb","messageID":"msg_d784d1985001JzAP2VoKuS7YVi","sessionID":"ses_287b378c1ffe854YLU3MLuwv1Z","type":"text","text":"The `proposal.md` file for AR-002 already exists at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md`. \n\nThe proposal document is complete and includes:\n\n- **Purpose**: Defines the CodeInterpreter CRD for managing code execution environments\n- **Scope**: Module `pkg/apis`, API group `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **In/Out of Scope**: Type definitions, registration, CRD manifests, validation (in scope); controller, kernel images, SDK (out of scope)\n- **Impact Analysis**: Dependencies, downstream consumers, breaking changes, migration path\n- **Alternatives Considered**: \n  1. Embed in AgentRuntime (rejected - couples lifecycles)\n  2. Use Jupyter Kernel Gateway directly (partially adopted - CRD manages Jupyter deployments)\n  3. One CRD per language (rejected - single CRD with language field is better)\n- **Implementation Plan**: 7 steps from scaffolding to tests\n- **Success Criteria**: 7 verification checkpoints\n- **References**: API conventions, controller-tools, code-generator, Jupyter docs","time":{"start":1775839820907,"end":1775839820907}}}
